<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="normal-adj">normal <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'nɔːml/    美 /'nɔːrml/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>正常的；平常的</strong></h4>
<p>typical, usual or expected：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>normal</strong> working hours / <strong>a normal life</strong>
正常的工作时间 / 生活</p></div>

<ul>
<li>it is normal (for sb) to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s normal for students to feel nervous before an exam.
学生在考试之前感到紧张是正常的。</p></div>

<h3 id="common-normal-ordinary-usual">辨析 common, normal, ordinary, usual</h3>
<p><strong>common</strong> 侧重表示普遍、常见。
<strong>normal</strong> 侧重指“正常的”、“平常的”。
<strong>ordinary</strong> 侧重表示平常、平凡、无奇特之处。形容人时可与common通用。
<strong>usual</strong> 表示由于长时间没有变化而形成了一种习惯或制度，强调习惯性。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He arrived later than usual. 
他到得比平时晚。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is usual for him to sit up late at night. 
他熬夜已成习惯。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>智力正常的；精神健全的</strong></h4>
<p>反 abnormal </p>
<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Such a blood pressure is  <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (正常的) for  a person of his age.  （ 2013 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. normal  </p></div>